<br>
They both said they have yet to see any solid blue mob be Dire Charmed. They said only mobs that can be dire charmed at lvl 60 are greens and light blues. If a mob cons blue they get the message &quot;target is immuned&quot;. Also once this happens they cant try again to recharm another mob for almost 2hours.<br>
Also the resist rate on Dire Charm is alot higher then normal charms. They both said they have gone as much as 10hours with every attempt to dire charm failing do to the mob being to high lvl, flagged as immune, or just normal resist.  <br>
<br>
There seems to be a ton of mobs flagged as immune to Dire charm that are lvl 46 or lower.  But both assured me that since they have had the skill (one has had it over 3 weeks) no solid blue con mob has been able to be Dire Charmed.  The enchanter that had the skill the longest said he had gone a few days without being able to Dire Charm a mob.  Every fail means another 2hour wait. Even if the mob is naturally immune to the skill or to high lvl, that is another 2hour wait.<br>
<br>
Most of my pets can kill a light blue or green mob solo with a damage shield, so maybe we have jumped the gun to quickly on dire charm. Which also explains why we were challenged by Verant to bring proof of mobs that can quad for 120+ and has 8k hps, that can be Dire Charmed.  Both enchanters laughed when I told them that example stating that no mob they have Dire Charmed so far can do this.<br>
<br>
When I told him that I had seen two enchanters that had Dire Charmed pets soloing in Sebillis they said with two light blue cons and there defensive skills that is possible but those pets are not hitting for that much and dont have anywhere near 8khps do to so many mobs being immune.  I have been one of the biggest advocates of seeing Dire Charm nerfed but if it is this limited we might be wasting our time bitching about this skill. Also if only light blues and greens can be dire charmed then I cant see this skill being better then the epic at all. Does anyone have real info on this skill? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 1236<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/02 8:54:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DIRE CHARM....FACT OR FICTION?</span><hr size=1> Yes I think Dire Charm is not nearly as big of a deal as we are making it out to be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usleethr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sleethr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/02 1:15:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DIRE CHARM....FA